a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Ensure adequate lighting is provided. Use portable lighting if required; 
c) A safety harness with a lifeline or fall arrest equipment must be worn, if working aloft; 
d) Consult 'Working Aloft' Risk Assessment, if required.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Sufficient number of crew to be made available for the task; 
c) Beware of lashing chains, wires, etc., under tension as they are liable to snap back when released; 
d) Ensure all crew pass the tools / lashing equipment in a safe manner; 
e) Consult 'Manual Handling' Risk Assessment.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided. Use portable lighting if required; 
c) Crew vigilance - Constant monitoring required.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided. Use portable lighting if required; 
c) All crew involved must wear an inflatable lifejacket; 
d) The vessel's course and speed are to be adjusted accordingly to minimise the effect of the weather conditions; 
e) Crew vigilance - Extreme caution when walking on deck; 
f) The risk of working on deck during adverse weather conditions is too high and therefore must be postponed until the weather improves.

a) All cargo lashing / securing equipment must be inspected and condition checked prior to every use; 
b) Any lashing / securing equipment found in poor condition or damaged must be removed immediately; 
c) All lashing must be carried out to the Master's satisfaction;

a) Permission must be obtained from the Master; 
b) Safe Work Permit to be issued; 
c) All crew involved to be briefed and a contingency / rescue plan in place and understood by all; 
d) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
e) Consult 'Enclosed Space Entry' Risk Assessment.
